parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of four-wheel drive can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The four-wheel drive system engages unexpectedly
causing the vehicle to lose traction or stability
especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctioning wipers can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: The wipers fail to operate properly
causing reduced visibility while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Turn Signals and Backup Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of turn signals and backup lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions or presence.
symptoms: The turn signals and backup lights fail to operate
making it difficult for other drivers to anticipate the vehicle's actions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The brakes grab or lock up unexpectedly
causing the vehicle to jerk or lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage properly
causing the vehicle to lose power or stall
especially when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or increased stopping distances, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes do not stop the vehicle properly
the brakes malfunction
the ABS system is faulty
the vehicle's brakes are unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Brake Hose Bracket on Upper Control Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the brake hose bracket can cause the brake hose to become pinched, leading to brake fluid leakage and failure to release the brakes, which can result in accidents, fires, or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brakes are hot
the brakes are stuck
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the brakes are leaking fluid
the vehicle is experiencing brake failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light stop switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights do not turn on or turn off intermittently
the brake lights stay on continuously
the brake lights do not turn off when the brake pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rainy or snowy conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers work occasionally but not consistently
especially when needed most
the wipers may stop working altogether
the wipers may work slowly or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty windshield wiper module can cause the wipers to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers work intermittently
the wipers may stop working altogether
the wipers may work slowly or erratically
the wiper motor has been checked and is functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken frame at the crossmember can cause loss of vehicle control, making it difficult to steer, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's steering becomes very difficult
the right front wheel "bows" outward
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair of a cracked frame can lead to a complete fracture, causing loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's steering becomes very difficult
the right front wheel "bows" outward
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
previous repairs to the frame may have been inadequate.
